speech:
Common symptoms:
fever,
tiredness,
dry cough.
Some people may experience:
aches and pains,
nasal congestion,
runny nose,
sore throat,
diarrhoea. dont worry even if u have these symptoms..self-isolate and visit the nearest health care!!!

It can vary from flu like symptoms such as
cold, cough, running nose, fever, altered
sense of taste and smell, generalised body
pain and can be as severe as
breathlessness, respiratory distress,
pneumonia etc.
It can also manifest as loose motions,
vomiting.
Sometimes it can present only as fever
lasting for greater than 72 hours with no
other relevant symptoms and not

responding to over the counter fever
medications such as paracetamol.
